From: Stephen Rothwell <sfr@canb.auug.org.au>
Date: Fri, 31 Aug 2018 07:47:28 +1000
Subject: disable stringop truncation warnings for now
Git-commit: 217c3e0196758662aa0429863b09d1c13da1c5d6
Patch-mainline: v4.19-rc2
References: git-fixes

They are too noisy

Signed-off-by: Stephen Rothwell <sfr@canb.auug.org.au>
Signed-off-by: Linus Torvalds <torvalds@linux-foundation.org>
Acked-by: Nicolas Saenz Julienne <nsaenzjulienne@suse.de>
---
 Makefile | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
index 2b458801ba74..a34a9283ee90 100644
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -807,6 +807,9 @@ KBUILD_CFLAGS += $(call cc-option,-Wdeclaration-after-statement,)
 # disable pointer signed / unsigned warnings in gcc 4.0
 KBUILD_CFLAGS += $(call cc-disable-warning, pointer-sign)
 
+# disable stringop warnings in gcc 8+
+KBUILD_CFLAGS += $(call cc-disable-warning, stringop-truncation)
+
 # disable invalid "can't wrap" optimizations for signed / pointers
 KBUILD_CFLAGS	+= $(call cc-option,-fno-strict-overflow)
 

